Fire has razed the new Lagos Metropolitan Area Transport Authority (LAMATA) terminal in Ajah. The cause of Saturday morning inferno is yet to be ascertained as videos on social media show thick smoke blowing through the roof. The state government however intervened swiftly by mobilizing the Fire Service Unit to the scene after emergency calls. Kogi: Angry Mob Sets Police Barrack Ablaze Over Slain Boy NAWOJ Advocates Justice For Hanifa, Others The Lagos State Transport Management Authority (LASTMA) has confirmed the inferno had been put out. It tweeted, “The earlier reported fire incident at LAMATA newly constructed shelter at Ajah is put off now. Normalcy has been restored”.